\sum_{n \ge 0}{(-1)^n a_n}
a_n=\begin{cases}2^{\frac{n}2+1},&\text{if }n\text{ is even}\\\\2^{\frac{n-1}2},&\text{if }n\text{ is odd}\;,\end{cases}
\sum_{n\ge 0}(-1)^na_n=2-1+4-2+8-4+16-8+\ldots\;.
\lim_{n\to\infty}\sum_{k=0}^n(-1)^ka_k=\infty\;.
